'''瓦洛厄山脈'''（{{lang-en|Wallowa Mountains}}）位於[[美國|美國]][[奧勒岡|奧勒岡]]州東北部的[[哥倫比亞高原|哥倫比亞高原]]。它的範圍在瓦洛厄區的西南部，從西北到東南涵蓋約40英里，介於西邊[[藍山山脈|藍山山脈]]和東邊[[蛇河|蛇河]]的中間。此範圍有時被認定為是藍山山脈向東延伸的一部分，而以奧勒岡的[[阿爾卑斯山|阿爾卑斯山]]稱之。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.opb.org/programs/ofg/segments/view/1739|title=老樹|year=2010|work=[[Oregon_Field_Guide|Oregon Field Guide]]|publisher=Oregon Public Broadcasting|accessdate=21 February 2010|archive-date=2017-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111225537/http://www.opb.org/programs/ofg/segments/view/1739|dead-url=no}}</ref> 此區大部分範圍被稱為[[鷹帽荒野|鷹帽荒野]]（Eagle Cap Wilderness），是[[瓦洛厄惠特曼國家森林|瓦洛厄惠特曼國家森林]]的一部分。

==地形==
此範圍由山脈東部的[[瓦洛厄河|瓦洛厄河]]及其支流，位於山脈西部的[[彌念河|彌念河]]（Minam River）所形成。而[[尹那哈河|尹那哈河]]（Imnaha River）則從山脈的東部流入會合。

此區域的最高點為[[薩卡賈維亞峰|薩卡賈維亞峰]]（Sacajawea Peak），在海拔{{convert|9838|ft|m|abbr=off}}的位置。<ref>{{cite web | title = 鷹帽荒野各高點之海拔高度 | publisher = U.S. Forest Service | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20050321002445/http://www.fs.fed.us/r6/w-w/recreation/wilderness/elevations-ecw.shtml | url = http://www.fs.fed.us/r6/w-w/recreation/wilderness/elevations-ecw.shtml | archivedate = 2005年3月21日 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>薩卡賈維亞峰是奧勒岡的第六高山峰，也是在本州中，除了[[喀斯喀特山脈|喀斯喀特山脈]]以外的第一高峰。<ref>Engeman, Richard H. (2009). ''The Oregon Companion: A Historical Gazetteer of the Useful, the Curious, and the Arcane''. Portland, Oregon: Timber Press. p. 393. ISBN 0-88192-899-2. {{OCLC|236142647}}.</ref>

==地質==

許多[[地質學家|地質學家]]相信在奧勒岡州東北部的瓦洛厄山脈是[[島嶼地帶|島嶼地帶]]（Insular Belt）分離的碎塊。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.washington.edu/burkemuseum/geo_history_wa/Coast%20Range%20Episode.htm |title=海岸地區集 |accessdate=25 May 2008 |publisher=The Burke Museum of Natural History and Culture |year=2006 |archive-date=2011-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629122538/http://www.washington.edu/burkemuseum/geo_history_wa/Coast%20Range%20Episode.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 瓦洛厄的中心部分由[[瓦洛厄岩基|瓦洛厄岩基]]環繞著[[哥倫比亞河|哥倫比亞河]][[玄武岩|玄武岩]]群所組成。<ref name = Krauskopf1943>{{cite journal| last = Krauskopf| first = K.B.| year = 1943| journal = American Journal of Science| volume = 241| issue = 10| pages = 607–628| url = http://www.ajsonline.org/content/241/10/607.full.pdf+html| accessdate = 16 October 2012| doi = 10.2475/ajs.241.10.607| title = 瓦洛厄岩基| archive-date = 2017-05-17| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170517213738/http://www.ajsonline.org/content/241/10/607.full.pdf+html| dead-url = no}}</ref> 此外，在岩基和玄武岩層之間，也有許多較老的岩層。<ref name = USGSCVO2004>{{cite web | title = 美國的火山往事 - 奧勒岡 | publisher = United States Geological Survey | date = 26 October 2004 | first = Lyn | last = Topinka | url = http://vulcan.wr.usgs.gov/LivingWith/VolcanicPast/Places/volcanic_past_oregon.html | accessdate = 18 November 2007 | archive-date = 2014-05-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140508042718/http://vulcan.wr.usgs.gov/LivingWith/VolcanicPast/Places/volcanic_past_oregon.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

瓦洛厄岩基是在[[侏儸紀|侏儸紀]]晚期和[[白堊紀|白堊紀]]早期（大約在一億六千萬年前和一億兩千萬年前）之間，由往上湧出的岩漿所造出的[[花崗岩|花崗岩]]所組成。<ref name = USGSCVO2004/>此岩石的配置，在熱帶海時期引起地層表面的上升。這可由在山脈中所出現的[[板岩|板岩]]、[[石英岩|石英岩]]及[[大理石|大理石]]得到證明；這些岩石是在[[三疊紀|三疊紀]]時期，由海洋沉積物所生成的岩石變形後所產生。<ref name = Warren1928>{{cite journal | title = 奧勒岡的物理和經濟地理學：第八章 瓦洛厄山脈和瓦洛厄郡 | last = Smith | first = Warren | journal = "The Commonwealth Review of the University of Oregon" | volume = 10 | issue = 1 | date = January 1928 | url = http://ir.library.oregonstate.edu/xmlui/bitstream/handle/1957/12051/Phy_Eco_Geo.pdf?sequence=1 | format = PDF | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | archive-date = 2017-08-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170817001500/http://ir.library.oregonstate.edu/xmlui/bitstream/handle/1957/12051/Phy_Eco_Geo.pdf?sequence=1 | dead-url = no }}</ref> 在岩基的中心部分為[[花崗閃長岩|花崗閃長岩]]，而其外圍的邊界地區則為[[石英閃長岩|石英閃長岩]]。<ref name=West1991>{{cite conference | title = 在奧勒岡瓦洛厄岩基中的鎂鐵飛地之起源 | last = West | first = Andrew | conference = 4th Keck Geology Consortium Undergraduate Research Symposium | location = Franklin and Marshall College | year = 1991 | url = http://keckgeology.org/node/1 | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120309123409/http://keckgeology.org/node/1 | archivedate = 2012年3月9日 }}</ref> 花崗岩岩基由深溝所切斷；<ref name = Mbalu1991>{{cite conference | title = Contact Metamorphic Effects of the Wallowa Batholith on the Hurwal Formation, Wallowa Mountains, Oregon | last = Mbalue | first = Chuma | conference = 4th Keck Geology Consortium Undergraduate Research Symposium | location = Franklin and Marshall College | year = 1991 | url = http://keckgeology.org/files/pdf/symvol/4th/Oregon/mbalu.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | archive-date = 2016-08-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160828022356/http://keckgeology.org/files/pdf/symvol/4th/Oregon/mbalu.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref> 但這種情形很少見。<ref name = West1991/>
[[File:Lostine_River_valley.jpg|thumb]]河谷]]

在[[更新世|更新世]]晚期，由於[[冰河|冰河]]的擠壓而塑造了一些山谷出來，而且也留下了一些[[冰磧石|冰磧石]]。<ref>{{cite journal | title = 更新世晚期時各種氣候及地形對於美國西部山中冰川作用的影響 | last = Thackray | first = Glenn | journal = Journal of Quaternary Science | year = 2008 | volume = 23 | issue = 6–7 | pages = 671–681 | url = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/jqs.1210/pdf | format = PDF | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | doi = 10.1002/jqs.1210 | archive-date = 2016-03-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160316100914/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/jqs.1210/pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref> 這一系列的冰磧石是由長時間的[[冰河推進|冰河推進]]和後退所形成。[[冰川沉積物|冰川沉積物]]也是這些山谷的共同特徵。<ref name=Budlong2005>{{cite journal | title = 奧勒岡東北部瓦洛厄湖的海洋生物分布學和沉積物 | last1 = Budlong | first1 = Bryce | last2 = Collier | last3 = Davis | first3 = Calvin | last4 = Gilbert | first4 = David | last5 = Legerwood | first5 = Rob | last6 = Tassel | first6 = Jay | journal = Eastern Oregon Geology | volume = 2 | date = September 2005 | url = http://www3.eou.edu/geology/easternoregongeology.html | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060909220012/http://www3.eou.edu/geology/easternoregongeology.html | archivedate = 2006年9月9日 }}</ref>冰河的溶解產生了相當大量的水，而這些水將沉澱物質沖刷到山谷的底部，形成了一層一層的沉積物，新的覆蓋在舊的沉積物之上面。<ref name=spokanecc>{{cite web|url=http://users.scc.spokane.edu/ABuddington/g210spr02/g3/geology.htm|title=一般地質學|date=Spring 2002|publisher=Spokane Community College|work=Wallowa Lake|first1=Logan|last1=Ditto|first2=Bryan|last2=Donaldson|accessdate=9 September 2013|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303210705/http://users.scc.spokane.edu/ABuddington/g210spr02/g3/geology.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==氣候==

在山脈中，大部分的降水都是以[[雪|雪]]的型態落下，降雪的尖峰時期為每年三月附近。<ref name="Rheinheimer2007">{{cite web | title = 格蘭德隆德河流域中氣候變遷對水文和生態的衝擊 | last = Rheinheimer | first = David | year = 2007 | url = https://www.geology.ucdavis.edu/shlemoncourse/trips/GrandeRonde/backgroundpapers/Rheinheimer.pdf | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | format = PDF | publisher = University of California, Davis | archive-date = 2010-06-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100614153805/https://www.geology.ucdavis.edu/shlemoncourse/trips/GrandeRonde/backgroundpapers/Rheinheimer.pdf | dead-url = yes }}</ref> 山脈中大部分的降水都是屬於[[地形降水|地形降水]]。在山頂附近每年的降水量可以超過2,500毫米，而在山谷中，則可以低到每年只有250毫米。<ref name=TaylorHale>{{cite web | title = 瓦洛厄郡之氣候 | last1 = Taylor | first1 = George | last2 = Hale | first2 = Candee | last3 = Joos | first3 = Sarah | url = http://www.ocs.oregonstate.edu/county_climate/Wallowa_files/Wallowa.html | work = Oregon Climate Service | publisher = Oregon State University | accessdate = 22 March 2012 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100611213019/http://www.ocs.oregonstate.edu/county_climate/Wallowa_files/Wallowa.html | archivedate = 2010年6月11日 }}</ref>

==生態==

相較於其周圍區域，瓦洛厄區山脈中的高降水量形成了中濕度性的[[棲息地|棲息地]]。<ref name = Crowe1997>{{cite web | title = Mid-Montane Wetland Plant Associations of the Malheur, Umatilla and Wallowa-Whitman National Forests | last = Crowe | first = Elizabeth A. | last2 = Clausnitzer | first2 = Rodrick R. | date = February 1997 | url = http://ir.library.oregonstate.edu/xmlui/bitstream/handle/1957/16061/MidMontaneWetlandPlantAssociationsWallowaWhitnf.pdf?sequence=1 | accessdate = 24 March 2012 | format = PDF | publisher = U.S. Forest Service | archive-date = 2017-08-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170818140931/http://ir.library.oregonstate.edu/xmlui/bitstream/handle/1957/16061/MidMontaneWetlandPlantAssociationsWallowaWhitnf.pdf?sequence=1 | dead-url = no }}</ref>在此區域生長的植物為附近[[洛磯山脈|洛磯山脈]]和[[喀斯喀特山脈|喀斯喀特山脈]]的組合。<ref name = Wells2006>{{cite web | last = Wells | first = Aaron | title = Deep Canyon and Subalpine Riparian and Wetland Plant Associations of the Malheur, Umatilla, and Wallowa-Whitman National Forests | date = November 2006 | url = http://ecoshare.info/uploads/publications/PNW-GTR-682.pdf | accessdate = 24 March 2012 | format = PDF | archive-date = 2019-06-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190602071354/https://ecoshare.info/uploads/publications/PNW-GTR-682.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref> 在低海拔地區，[[道格拉斯杉|道格拉斯杉]]（Douglas fir）為斜坡上最常見的樹種。而[[英國針樅|英國針樅]]（Engelmann spruce）和[[美國黑松|美國黑松]]（lodgepole pine）則生長在山谷的底部。在海拔低於1,600公尺的地區[[大冷杉|大冷杉]]（grand fir）則是常見的植物。<ref>{{cite web | title = 在奧勒岡瓦洛厄山脈鷹帽荒野中兩種排水系統下的植物 | last = Cole | first = David | year = 1982 | url = http://content.lib.umt.edu/cdm/singleitem/collection/forest/id/321/rec/20 | accessdate = 24 March 2012 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131221191152/http://content.lib.umt.edu/cdm/singleitem/collection/forest/id/321/rec/20 | archivedate = 2013年12月21日 }}</ref> 在附近有泉水的草地中，則常會有柳樹和鮮苔。<ref name = Wells2006/> 在海拔高度高於2,100公尺的地區，則完全是[[亞高山冷杉|亞高山冷杉]]（subalpine fir），而[[美國白皮松|美國白皮松]]（whitebark pine）則常出現在山脊和向南的斜坡上。<ref name=johnson>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fs.fed.us/pnw/gtr569.pdf|title=綠色牛尾草牧場：瓦洛厄山脈中的時光變遷|first=Charles G.|last=Johnson, Jr.|date=February 2003|work=General Technical Report PNW-GTR-569|publisher=U.S. Forest Service|page=8|accessdate=9 September 2013}}</ref>

==歷史==

此區域為瓦洛厄之[[下內茲佩爾賽人|下內茲佩爾賽人]]（Lower Nez Perce）的故鄉。這些內茲佩爾賽人居住於峽谷中，用有計劃地燃燒樹林的方式建立牧草地，以繁殖他們在大約西元1730年時所獲得的馬匹。<ref name=Williams2005>{{cite web | title = 瓦洛厄郡的放牧歷史 | last1 = Williams | first1 = Jennifer | last2 = Melville | first2 = Erin | date = September 2005 | page = 7 | publisher = Oregon State University | url = http://extension.oregonstate.edu/wallowa/sites/default/files/_in_Wallowa_County_Compilation_edited_4_2009.pdf | accessdate = 24 March 2012 | format = PDF | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110115070850/http://extension.oregonstate.edu/wallowa/sites/default/files/_in_Wallowa_County_Compilation_edited_4_2009.pdf | archive-date = 2011-01-15 | dead-url = yes }}</ref> 在西元1834年，[[邦納維爾上校|邦納維爾上校]]（Captain Bonneville）在他前往[[瓦拉瓦拉要塞|瓦拉瓦拉要塞]]（Fort Walla Walla），而橫越這些山脈時，遇見了下內茲佩爾賽人。<ref name = Irving1861>{{cite book | title = 邦納維爾上校的冒險 | last = Irving | first = Washington |  year = 1861 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=2_4htIWyuWEC&pg=PA19&dq=captain+bonneville+and+the+nez+perce#v=onepage&q&f=false | accessdate = 24 March 2012}}</ref>在西元1840年代，許多人開始向西部移動，為此地帶來了一些移民，而內茲佩爾賽人也開始和這些移民有了貿易往來。<ref name = Williams2005/> 在西元1861年時，有一個開墾地在山脈中被建立起來。<ref name=Lawson2007>{{cite web | title = 奧勒岡州格蘭德隆德流域的土地和資源使用歷史 | last = Lawson | first = Abigail J. | year = 2007 | url = https://www.geology.ucdavis.edu/~shlemoncourse/trips/GrandeRonde/backgroundpapers/Lawson.pdf | publisher = University of California, Davis | accessdate = 24 March 2012 | format = PDF | archive-date = 2013-12-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131216005922/https://www.geology.ucdavis.edu/~shlemoncourse/trips/GrandeRonde/backgroundpapers/Lawson.pdf | dead-url = yes }}</ref> 在西元1863年，一項新的協定被簽署，將在根據西元1855年協定所取得的土地全部轉授與美國政府。在同一年，這些在山中的移民遷移到今日的[[拉格蘭德|拉格蘭德]]（La Grande），這些區域包括瓦洛厄山谷，此為[[约瑟夫酋長|约瑟夫酋長]]的故鄉。<ref name = Lawson2007/> 在西元1867年，政府第一次開放移民到瓦洛厄山谷。<ref name = Williams2005/>之後土地勘測員開始進駐丈量，一直到西元1869年為止。<ref name = Josephy1965>{{cite book | last = Josephy | first = Alvin | title = 內茲佩爾賽印地安人和西北的開啟 | url = http://books.google.com/?id=D1Ffhzz0UOkC&pg=PR7&dq=captain+bonneville+and+the+nez+perce#v=onepage&q&f=false | year = 1965 | isbn = 9780395850114}}</ref> 在西元1873年，瓦洛厄山谷被分割成兩半，一半分配給內茲佩爾賽人<ref name = Buckendorf2001>{{cite web | title = 西元1800到1950年間在大賀爾峽谷區的移民探險、屯墾及土地使用 | last = Buckendorf | first = Madeline | last2 = Bauer | first2 = Barbara | last3 = Jacox | first3 = Elizabeth | year = 2001 | url = http://www.idahopower.com/pdfs/Relicensing/hellscanyon/hellspdfs/techappendices/Cultural/e04_11.pdf | accessdate = 24 March 2012 | format = PDF | archive-date = 2016-03-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160305063814/http://www.idahopower.com/pdfs/Relicensing/hellscanyon/hellspdfs/techappendices/Cultural/e04_11.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>，另一半分配給移民。<ref name = Williams2005/> 兩年以後，在西元1875年，美國政府禁止內茲佩爾賽人離開山谷。<ref name = Buckendorf2001/> 進入山谷的第一條路在同一年被建造完成。<ref name = Williams2005/> 在西元1877年，美國政府試圖強迫內茲佩爾賽人移居；但是因此激怒了原住民。原住民選擇了突襲移民者，而引起了[[內茲佩爾賽戰爭|內茲佩爾賽戰爭]]（Nez Perce War）。<ref name = Lawson2007/>

伐木業者在西元1880年末期進入此山區，他們利用小溪和河流運送木材。<ref name = Lawson2007/> 在西元1884年，瓦洛厄湖上的一個水壩被建造完成以灌溉該山谷。而第一條進入此山谷的鐵路則於西元1908年完成。<ref name = Williams2005/> 在西元1919年，[[聯合太平洋鐵道公司|聯合太平洋鐵道公司]]（Union Pacific Railroad）建造了通往山谷上方的鐵路，以便更安全地運送木材。<ref name = Lawson2007/> 在西元1916年，瓦洛厄湖下方的水壩被水泥材質水壩取代，而於西元1929年，一個全新的水壩則被建造完成。<ref name = Williams2005/>

